PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1780589464
OL,3,CHealthy Ageing: What Should You Eat?
OL,5,FIn a long-term study, led by Stanford
OL,6,FUniversity, scientists at The
OL,7,FUniversity of Manchester have
OL,8,Funcovered a link between where you
OL,9,Flive and how quickly your body ages.
OL,11,FEast Asians living outside Asia were
OL,12,Fbiologically older than those who
OL,13,Fstayed in Asia. Europeans showed the
OL,14,Fopposite pattern, appearing
OL,15,Fbiologically younger when living
OL,16,Foutside Europe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1780589464
OL,3,CHealthy Ageing: What Should You Eat?
OL,5,F"It really shows for the first time
OL,6,Fhow you can pull apart this
OL,7,Finteraction between genetics and where
OL,8,Fyou're from, and how your environment
OL,9,Fand your diet being part of that
OL,10,Fenvironment can affect how you age." -
OL,11,FProfessor Richard Unwin, The
OL,12,FUniversity of Manchester
OL,14,FThe programme also looks at specific
OL,15,Fexamples of food which could help us
OL,16,Fto age better.
OL,26,@mD@AOUrD@dO]
